<div class="agreement-doc space-y-3">
  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 pt-2 first:pt-0 border-t border-gray-200 first:border-0 mt-2 first:mt-0">General Service Agreement</h3>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">Background</h4>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>Qualifications and Technology. Client acknowledges that Holistic Business Solutions Inc. (“HBS”) possesses the qualifications, experience, personnel, and technology-enabled infrastructure necessary to provide the services described in this Agreement. HBS agrees to provide such services to Client through a combination of professional expertise and its proprietary online platform, Hadari (also referred to as the HBS Client Portal), together with any related systems, tools, automations, and support resources, in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement.</li>
    <li>Governing Law and Compliance. The Parties acknowledge that the professional healthcare services rendered by Client to its patients remain solely the responsibility of Client, including compliance with all laws, regulations, licensing requirements, scope-of-practice rules, documentation standards, and payer requirements applicable to Client’s practice and the services provided to patients. Holistic Business Solutions is responsible only for compliance with the laws and regulations applicable to the billing, administrative, and technology-enabled services it provides on behalf of Client under this Agreement.</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-gray-700">HBS shall perform the Services in compliance with all applicable federal, state, and local laws relating to the Services, including, where applicable, the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996 (“HIPAA”), the Health Information Technology for Economic and Clinical Health Act (“HITECH”), and other applicable privacy, security, and data-protection laws. HBS shall maintain commercially reasonable and industry-standard administrative, physical, and technical safeguards designed to preserve the security, confidentiality, integrity, and availability of all Client and patient information transmitted to, stored within, or processed through Hadari.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-700">IN CONSIDERATION of the mutual promises and benefits contained in this Agreement, the adequacy and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, the Client and HBS (each, a “Party” and together, the “Parties”) agree as follows:</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">1. Services Provided</h4>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>Engagement of HBS. The Client hereby engages HBS to perform professional medical billing and related administrative services (the “Services”) as defined in this Agreement and further detailed in Exhibit A – Tiered Scope of Services. The specific scope of Services applicable to the Client shall correspond to the service tier and percentage rate selected at the time of Onboarding.</li>
    <li>Definition of Medical Billing. For the purposes of this Agreement, “medical billing” includes the coding, generation and submission of claims to the relevant payer(s) for services rendered by the Client. Medical billing also encompasses the secure management of documentation requests and follow‑up activities related to claim status—including rejections, denials and appeals—consistent with the Client’s selected tier.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">2. Term of Agreement</h4>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>Term. This Agreement shall commence on the effective date and continue on a month‑to‑month basis unless and until terminated in accordance with this Section.</li>
    <li>Termination for Convenience. Either Party may terminate this Agreement upon thirty (30) days’ written notice to the other Party. Upon termination, HBS shall be entitled to any compensation earned for Services performed prior to the termination date in accordance with this Agreement.</li>
    <li>Termination for Breach or Non‑Payment. In the event either Party breaches a material provision of this Agreement, the non‑defaulting Party may terminate this Agreement immediately and require the defaulting Party to indemnify the non‑defaulting Party against all reasonable damages. HBS may also terminate immediately in the event of the Client’s non‑payment.</li>
    <li>Mutual Termination. This Agreement may be terminated at any time by mutual written agreement of the Parties.</li>
    <li>Effect of Termination. Except as otherwise provided in this Agreement, the obligations of HBS will end upon the effective date of termination. The Client remains responsible for payment of any outstanding fees due under this Agreement.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">3. Performance of HBS</h4>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>Best Efforts. The Parties agree to take all actions reasonably necessary to give full effect to the terms of this Agreement.</li>
    <li>Continuous Services. HBS shall perform the Services on a continuous (“rolling”) basis, consistent with the Client’s ongoing operations and claim‑submission needs.</li>
    <li>Use of Hadari. To facilitate efficient, accurate, and secure delivery of the Services, the Parties agree that Hadari, the online client portal operated by Holistic Business Solutions, shall serve as the primary system of record for the transmission, storage, and management of patient information, encounter data, claims information, communications, documents, and other information relating to the Services, unless otherwise expressly agreed in writing by the Parties</li>
    <li>Timely Processing. HBS shall process claims submitted through Hadari in a timely manner to minimize delays in claim submission and reimbursement. HBS is not responsible for payer reimbursement amounts or timelines.</li>
    <li>Denial and Rejection Handling. HBS shall make commercially reasonable efforts to follow up on, and when appropriate resubmit, any rejected or denied claims. The scope of follow‑up activities is limited to the level defined within the Client’s selected service tier under Exhibit A. HBS may request from the Client any additional information or documentation necessary to facilitate payment.</li>
    <li>Document Requests. HBS shall submit electronic copies of documentation requested by payer(s) on behalf of the Client, contingent upon the Client making such materials available through Hadari or, if agreed, by email, fax or via the Client’s EMR/EHR system.</li>
    <li>Data Security. HBS shall maintain administrative, physical and technical safeguards to ensure the secure storage and transmission of all patient data in compliance with applicable local, state and federal laws and regulations, including but not limited to HIPAA.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">4. Client Responsibilities</h4>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>Portal Use. The Client shall submit all patient and encounter information through Hadari, which serves as the designated system of record for claim generation and processing.</li>
    <li>Data Accuracy. The Client shall provide complete and accurate patient data, including name, address, date of birth, policy numbers and any other demographic or payer‑related identifiers required for claim submission.</li>
    <li>Service Details. The Client shall provide accurate date(s) of service, duration of service(s), rendering provider(s) and, when applicable, current prescriptions, referrals or authorizations through Hadari.</li>
    <li>Indemnification for Data Errors. The Client agrees to indemnify HBS for any errors, denials or adverse actions arising from inaccurate, incomplete or false information submitted by the Client.</li>
    <li>Billing Requirements. The Client acknowledges that HBS will not bill for services when required supporting documentation is incomplete, expired or otherwise non‑compliant with payer requirements. This includes, but is not limited to, out‑of‑date prescriptions, missing or invalid referrals, authorizations, plan‑of‑care renewals or clinical documentation necessary to establish medical necessity.</li>
    <li>Operational Changes. The Client shall promptly notify HBS of any material changes to its billing processes, payer participation, documentation procedures or internal workflows. Substantive modifications may require an amended agreement or updated configuration within Hadari.</li>
    <li>Data Integrity. The Client retains sole responsibility for the accuracy, validity and completeness of all clinical, demographic and payer information entered or transmitted through Hadari. HBS shall not be liable for claim denials, delays or compliance actions arising from inaccurate or incomplete data provided by the Client. The Client is solely responsible for ensuring services rendered to patients comply with professional and payer standards of care.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">5. Currency</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Except as otherwise provided in this Agreement, all monetary amounts referred to herein are stated in U.S. dollars.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">6. Compensation</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">1. Service Fees. Client shall compensate Holistic Business Solutions Inc. for Services in accordance with the service tier, percentage rate, and fee structure selected by Client during onboarding through Hadari and reflected in Client’s account records on file, as may be updated from time to time in accordance with this Agreement and Exhibit A – Tiered Scope of Services. Unless otherwise expressly agreed in writing within Hadari or by email between the Parties, the standard fee schedule is as follows:</p>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Client’s selected tier, onboarding fee payment, and any subsequent changes accepted through Hadari shall be deemed incorporated into and made part of this Agreement without the need for a separate signed order form or amendment.</p>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>Service Fee: A percentage of amounts actually reimbursed by the payer to Client or, where applicable, directly to HBS on Client’s behalf, based on the service tier selected by Client in Hadari:</li>
    <li>6% Tier: 6% of reimbursed amounts</li>
    <li>7% Tier: 7% of reimbursed amounts</li>
    <li>8% Tier: 8% of reimbursed amounts</li>
    <li>9% Tier: 9% of reimbursed amounts</li>
    <li>Deductible Claim Fee: $10.00 per claim where the claim is processed and applied entirely or primarily toward a patient deductible and no insurance reimbursement is issued.</li>
    <li>Onboarding Fee: A one-time onboarding fee of $500.00, due and payable at the time Client electronically accepts this Agreement and completes onboarding through Hadari.</li>
    <li>Invoice Schedule. HBS shall issue invoices on or about the first (1st) day of each calendar month for Services rendered and reimbursements received within the preceding calendar month.</li>
    <li>Payment Terms. Invoices are due and payable on the fifteenth (15th) day of each month unless otherwise specified in writing. Late payments may be subject to suspension of Services or other remedies as permitted under this Agreement. Reinstatement of Services does not waive HBS’s right to collect any overdue balances.</li>
    <li>Expenses. Except as expressly stated herein, HBS shall not be reimbursed for incidental or administrative expenses incurred in the course of providing Services under this Agreement.</li>
    <li>Suspension for Non‑Payment. If payment is not received within fifteen (15) days of the due date, and no alternative arrangement has been confirmed in writing by HBS, the Client’s account access will automatically convert to read‑only status until payment is received in full. During this suspension period, the Client will retain access to view historical claim data and reports but will be unable to submit new claims or make account modifications. Normal access will be restored promptly upon receipt of payment.</li>
    <li>Tier Changes the Client may request a change in service tier at any time by written notice through the HBS Client Portal (Hadari) or by email. Any approved tier change will take effect on the first day of the following calendar month following HBS’s written confirmation. All Services rendered prior to that effective date shall be billed at the rate and terms applicable to the Client’s current tier, without proration or retroactive adjustment. HBS reserves the right to a brief account review prior to implementing a tier change to ensure alignment of services, compliance, and billing configuration. Except as expressly modified by an approved tier change, all other terms and conditions of this Agreement, including Exhibits A and B, shall remain in full force and effect.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">7. Confidentiality</h4>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>Definition. “Confidential Information” includes any non‑public data or information relating to either Party’s business, systems or clients, including but not limited to patient data, billing information, business processes, access credentials and proprietary technology, whether disclosed orally, electronically or in writing.</li>
    <li>Mutual Obligations. Each Party agrees not to disclose, use or reproduce any Confidential Information except as required to perform its obligations under this Agreement or as required by law. If required under HIPAA, the Parties shall enter into a separate Business Associate Agreement (BAA), which shall govern the handling of protected health information.</li>
    <li>Safeguards. HBS shall implement administrative, physical and technical safeguards to protect all Confidential Information transmitted or stored through Hadari, consistent with HIPAA and other applicable data‑protection laws.</li>
    <li>Client Credentials. The Client agrees to maintain the confidentiality of its Hadari credentials and to restrict system access to authorized personnel only.</li>
    <li>Duration. The confidentiality obligations in this section shall remain in effect during the Term and survive indefinitely following termination of this Agreement.</li>
    <li>Incorporation of Exhibit B – Business Associate Agreement The Client acknowledges that HBS’s Services may involve access to information constituting Protected Health Information (“PHI”) under HIPAA. Accordingly, the Business Associate Agreement (Exhibit B) is incorporated by reference and governs HBS’s handling of PHI. This incorporation applies to all Clients who qualify as Covered Entities or who, in the ordinary course of using HBS’s Services, transmit or maintain PHI. The BAA remains in full force and effect for the duration of this Agreement and any renewals or tier changes.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">8. Ownership of Intellectual Property</h4>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>HBS Intellectual Property. All intellectual property rights, including all software, source code, object code, documentation, workflows, templates, automations, configurations, designs, interfaces, processes, trade secrets, and other related materials developed, deployed, provided, or utilized by Holistic Business Solutions in connection with Hadari, the delivery of the Services, or any related systems, features, or functionality, together with any modifications, enhancements, derivative works, or improvements thereto, shall remain the sole and exclusive property of HBS.</li>
    <li>Client Data. The Client retains ownership of all business records, patient data and any information uploaded or generated through Hadari. HBS shall use Client Data solely as necessary to provide the Services, comply with applicable law, fulfill its obligations under this Agreement and the BAA, and maintain, secure, support, or improve Hadari and related services. HBS shall not sell Client Data.</li>
    <li>License. HBS grants the Client a non‑exclusive, limited‑use license to access and use Hadari and related tools for the duration of this Agreement, consistent with the service tier selected.</li>
    <li>No Transfer. Nothing in this Agreement shall be construed as transferring ownership of HBS’s underlying software, code or platform architecture to the Client.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">9. Capacity / Independent Contractor</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">In performing the Services under this Agreement, HBS acts as an independent contractor and not as an employee, agent or partner of the Client. Nothing in this Agreement shall be construed to create a joint venture, partnership or employment relationship. The Services are delivered through HBS’s proprietary technology platform and operational infrastructure, but all workflows, methodologies and business decisions remain under HBS’s independent control. The Client shall not exercise supervision or control over HBS’s methods or internal processes.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">10. Right of Substitution</h4>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>Use of Subcontractors. HBS may, at its discretion, engage subcontractors, third‑party service providers or integrated software partners to perform or support portions of the Services, including data processing, clearinghouse functions or automation within Hadari.</li>
    <li>Responsibility and Compliance. HBS shall remain fully responsible for the performance of any subcontractor or technology partner and shall ensure that all such entities are bound by confidentiality and compliance obligations consistent with this Agreement. HBS shall execute Business Associate Agreements or equivalent data‑protection contracts with all subcontractors who may access protected health information.</li>
    <li>Payment. Compensation remains payable by the Client exclusively to HBS, regardless of whether HBS engages any third party in the delivery of Services.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">11. Autonomy</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Except as otherwise stated in this Agreement, HBS retains full control over its working time, methods, technology and decision‑making processes in providing the Services. HBS shall operate autonomously, utilizing its proprietary systems and automation tools, while remaining responsive to the reasonable needs and inquiries of the Client.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">12. Equipment</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Except as otherwise provided in this Agreement, HBS shall provide and maintain, at its own expense, all equipment, software, subscriptions and digital infrastructure required to perform the Services, including Hadari and related automation systems. The Client is responsible for maintaining its own hardware, internet connection and internal systems necessary to securely access Hadari and submit information required for claim processing.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">13. Data Ownership and Return upon Termination</h4>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>Data Ownership. All patient, claim and business data entered, transmitted or generated by the Client through Hadari shall remain the property of the Client. HBS acknowledges that it acts solely as a data processor or business associate, as applicable, in handling such information.</li>
    <li>Data Export. Upon termination or expiration of this Agreement, and upon written request from the Client made within thirty (30) days of termination, HBS shall make available to the Client a secure export of all Client‑owned data maintained within Hadari in a commercially reasonable format (e.g., CSV or comparable file type).</li>
    <li>Deletion. After the data‑export window has elapsed, HBS may permanently delete Client data from its active systems, subject to applicable legal or regulatory record‑retention requirements. HBS shall have no obligation to maintain or store Client data beyond the retention period set forth in this Agreement and shall not be liable for data deleted or purged in accordance with this clause.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">14. Notice</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">All formal notices, requests, consents, approvals, demands, or other communications required or permitted under this Agreement shall be in writing and delivered by electronic mail to the email addresses designated by the Parties during onboarding through Hadari or as subsequently updated in writing or within Hadari.</p>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>Client: The primary email address associated with the Client&#39;s account in Hadari at the time notice is sent. </li>
    <li>HBS: legal@holisticbusinesssolutions.com</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Notice shall be deemed given on the date and time the email is transmitted, provided that the sending Party does not receive an automated notice of non-delivery, rejection, or invalid address. Communications, messages, comments, alerts, support tickets, and other operational or service-related correspondence transmitted through Hadari may be relied upon by the Parties for routine account administration, support, billing, encounter management, claim processing, and other day-to-day matters. Such communications shall not constitute formal notice under this Agreement unless the applicable provision expressly permits notice through Hadari.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">15. Indemnification</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Except to the extent paid in settlement from any applicable insurance policies and to the extent permitted by law, each Party shall indemnify and hold harmless the other Party, and its respective directors, shareholders, affiliates, officers, agents, employees and permitted successors and assigns, from and against any and all claims, losses, damages, liabilities, penalties, punitive damages, expenses and reasonable legal fees that result from or arise out of that Party’s negligence, willful misconduct or breach of this Agreement. This indemnification shall survive the termination of this Agreement.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">16. Modification of Agreement</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Any amendment or modification of this Agreement or any additional obligation assumed by either Party shall be binding only if evidenced in writing and accepted electronically by the Parties through Hadari, by email confirmation, or by other written electronic record.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">17. Time of the Essence</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Time is of the essence in this Agreement. No extension or variation of this Agreement shall operate as a waiver of this provision.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">18. Assignment</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">HBS may assign or transfer its rights and obligations under this Agreement to any affiliated entity or successor in interest upon written notice to the Client. The Client may not assign or transfer its obligations without HBS’s prior written consent.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">19. Entire Agreement</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">This Agreement, together with all referenced exhibits constitutes the entire agreement between the Parties with respect to its subject matter. There are no representations, warranties, collateral agreements or conditions affecting this Agreement except as expressly stated herein.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">20. Enurement</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">This Agreement shall enure to the benefit of and be binding upon the Parties and their respective heirs, executors, administrators and permitted successors and assigns.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">21. Titles / Headings</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Headings are inserted for convenience only and shall not affect the interpretation of this Agreement.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">22. Interpretation</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Words in the singular include the plural and vice versa. Words in one gender include all genders. References to “including” mean “including without limitation”.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">23. Governing Law</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of New York, without regard to its conflict-of-law principles, and applicable federal law. To the extent applicable to the services or data at issue, the Parties shall also comply with any state privacy or security laws that provide greater protection than applicable federal law.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">24. Severability</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">If any provision of this Agreement is held to be invalid or unenforceable in whole or in part, the remaining provisions shall nevertheless continue in full force and effect.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">25. Waiver</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">The waiver by either Party of a breach, default, delay or omission of any of the provisions of this Agreement by the other Party shall not be construed as a waiver of any subsequent breach of the same or other provisions.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">Electronic Acceptance and Execution</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">By electronically accepting this Agreement through Hadari, the authorized representative of Client represents and warrants that they have authority to bind Client to this Agreement. Client’s electronic acceptance, together with the associated system-generated records maintained by Hadari, including the date and time of acceptance, user account information, IP address, and related metadata, shall constitute Client’s legally binding signature and execution of this Agreement. Client: The legal entity, business name, and authorized representative information provided during onboarding through Hadari. Holistic Business Solutions: This Agreement is accepted and executed by HBS upon activation of Client’s account, commencement of Services, or other electronic confirmation by HBS within Hadari.</p>
  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 pt-2 first:pt-0 border-t border-gray-200 first:border-0 mt-2 first:mt-0">Exhibit A – Tiered Scope of Services</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700">The following service descriptions define the scope of work to be performed by HBS under this Agreement. The applicable service tier shall be determined by the percentage rate selected by the Client at onboarding. Each successive tier includes all services listed in the preceding tiers, except where otherwise specified.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">Incorporation Clause</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">This Exhibit A is hereby incorporated by reference into the General Service Agreement between HBS and the Client. All terms and conditions of the Agreement apply equally to this Exhibit. In the event of any inconsistency between the provisions of this Exhibit and the Agreement, the terms of the Agreement shall control.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">Scope Limitation Clause</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Only the services associated with the service tier currently selected by Client and reflected within Client’s account in Hadari shall apply. The inclusion of descriptions of other service tiers in this Exhibit does not grant Client any right or entitlement to those services unless and until Client selects and HBS accepts such tier within Hadari.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">6 % Tier — Core</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">At the six percent (6 %) service level, HBS shall provide fundamental billing functions necessary to facilitate the submission and reconciliation of insurance claims. Services include: 1. Claim Submission: Preparation and electronic transmission of claims to payers through the designated clearinghouse. 2. Document Submission: Secure handling and submission of all documentation required to support claim processing. 3. Payment Posting: Entry and reconciliation of remittance data and payments received. 4. Basic Dashboard Access: Provision of access to a standard dashboard reflecting claim and payment activity. No eligibility verification, denial management or follow‑up activities are included at this tier.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">7 % Tier — Streamlined</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">At the seven percent (7 %) service level, HBS shall provide all services included in the “Core” tier together with additional verification and limited denial‑management functions designed to improve claim acceptance rates. Additional services include: 1. Eligibility Verification: Confirmation of patient coverage and benefits prior to claim submission. 2. Basic Denial Management: Submission of reconsiderations to the payer for standard claim denials, limited to two (2) attempts. This tier adds eligibility verification and basic denial reconsideration processing.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">8 % Tier — Growth</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">At the eight percent (8 %) service level, HBS shall provide all services included in the “Streamlined” tier together with expanded claim‑resolution capabilities and analytic reporting intended to optimize revenue performance. Additional services include: 1. Advanced Denial Management: Comprehensive review and resolution of complex or repeated denials. 2. Corrected Claims: Preparation and resubmission of corrected claims in response to payer‑identified processing discrepancies or other adjustment requirements. 3. Payer Calls: Direct communication with insurance carriers to clarify or expedite claim adjudication. 4. Advanced Dashboard and KPI Access: Enhanced data visualization and performance metrics concerning reimbursement trends and collection efficiency. This tier adds advanced denial resolution, corrected‑claim processing, payer communication and expanded analytical reporting features.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">9 % Tier — Complete</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">At the nine percent (9 %) service level, HBS shall provide all services included in the “Growth” tier together with comprehensive revenue‑cycle oversight and priority administrative support. Additional services include: 1. Complete Denial Management: End‑to‑end pursuit and resolution of all denied, unpaid or underpaid claims. 2. Quarterly Audits: Systematic review of claims and documentation for accuracy, compliance and trend identification. 3. Appeals Management: Preparation and submission of formal written appeals to payers as necessary. 4. Priority Support: Client support tickets are designated as high priority within HBS’s internal support system and queued ahead of standard support requests. HBS will make commercially reasonable efforts to expedite acknowledgment and resolution; however, no guaranteed resolution timeframe is offered. 5. Scheduled Reports: Automatic delivery of periodic financial and performance reports. 6. CSV Exports: Provision of downloadable datasets for the Client’s internal use or integration with external systems. This tier constitutes full‑service revenue management with the highest level of support and reporting provided by HBS.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">Acknowledgment</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">The Client acknowledges that Services are provided strictly in accordance with the service tier selected by Client and the corresponding rates and fees reflected in Hadari at the time of onboarding or as subsequently modified in accordance with this Agreement. Any services requested by Client that fall outside the scope of the selected tier may, at HBS’s discretion, be subject to additional fees, charges, or revised pricing and shall require a separate written agreement, amendment, email confirmation, or acceptance within Hadari before such services are provided. Tier modifications shall be governed by Section 6.6 of this Agreement.</p>
  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 pt-2 first:pt-0 border-t border-gray-200 first:border-0 mt-2 first:mt-0">Exhibit B – Business Associate Agreement (BAA)</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Effective Date: The “Effective Date” of this Business Associate Agreement shall be the date and time at which the Covered Entity electronically accepts this Business Associate Agreement through Hadari, as reflected in the system-generated records maintained by Hadari, including the date and time of acceptance, user account information, IP address, and related metadata. Between: • Covered Entity: The legal entity identified by the Client during onboarding, together with the business name and address provided in the Client account profile at the time of electronic acceptance. • Business Associate: Holistic Business Solutions, including its affiliated personnel, contractors, and systems used in connection with the services provided under this Agreement. This Business Associate Agreement (“BAA”) supplements and forms part of the General Service Agreement (“GSA”) between the Parties. It governs the handling, protection and permitted use of Protected Health Information (“PHI”) in compliance with the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996 (“HIPAA”), the Health Information Technology for Economic and Clinical Health Act (“HITECH”) and all applicable regulations at 45 C.F.R. Parts 160 and 164.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">1. Purpose and Scope</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Use of the HBS Portal. PHI may be transmitted through, processed or stored within Hadari or associated systems in connection with billing and administrative services performed by HBS on behalf of the Covered Entity. Compliance with Laws. HBS agrees to use and disclose PHI only as permitted by this BAA and applicable law. The Covered Entity remains responsible for ensuring that its use of the HBS Portal complies with HIPAA and other applicable privacy‑and‑security regulations.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">2. Permitted Uses and Disclosures</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Performance of Services. HBS may use or disclose PHI solely to perform the functions, activities or services described in the GSA, provided such use or disclosure would not violate HIPAA or HITECH if performed by the Covered Entity. Internal Operations. HBS may use PHI for its internal management, operations or legal‑compliance purposes and to report violations of law as permitted under 45 C.F.R. § 164.502(j). Marketing Prohibition. HBS shall not use PHI to market to any individual or sell PHI.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">3. Safeguards and Security</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Security Program. HBS shall implement administrative, physical and technical safeguards reasonably designed to protect the confidentiality, integrity and availability of PHI. Policies and Training. HBS shall maintain written policies and procedures addressing HIPAA security and privacy compliance and ensure that all employees and subcontractors receive appropriate training.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">4. Subcontractors</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">HBS shall ensure that any subcontractor or third‑party service provider that may access PHI agrees in writing to substantially similar restrictions, conditions and safeguards that apply to HBS under this BAA.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">5. Breach Notification</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Notification Obligation. HBS shall notify the Covered Entity of any unauthorized use or disclosure of PHI, or any breach of unsecured PHI, without unreasonable delay and in no case later than sixty (60) calendar days after discovery[1]. Contents of Notice. Such notice shall include, to the extent known, the nature of the breach, the individuals affected and steps taken to mitigate potential harm.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">6. Access, Amendment and Accounting</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Access. To the extent applicable, HBS shall provide the Covered Entity with access to PHI in a Designated Record Set to meet the requirements of 45 C.F.R. § 164.524. Amendments. HBS shall make amendments to PHI as directed by the Covered Entity under 45 C.F.R. § 164.526. Accounting of Disclosures. HBS shall maintain and provide information necessary for the Covered Entity to respond to requests for an accounting of disclosures under 45 C.F.R. § 164.528.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">7. Return or Deletion of PHI</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Upon termination of the GSA or this BAA, HBS shall, at the Covered Entity’s written request, provide a secure export of all PHI maintained on its systems and thereafter permanently delete such PHI from its active systems consistent with its data‑retention policy. If return or deletion of PHI is infeasible, HBS shall continue to protect such PHI under this BAA for as long as it is retained.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">8. Compliance Documentation</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Upon reasonable written request, HBS shall make available documentation necessary to demonstrate compliance with its HIPAA and HITECH obligations. On‑site inspections shall not be required unless mandated by law or regulatory authority.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">9. Notices</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">All notices, requests, approvals, consents, breach notifications, termination notices, or other communications required or permitted under this Business Associate Agreement shall be in writing and delivered by electronic mail to the contact addresses designated by the Parties during onboarding through Hadari, or to such other email address as either Party may subsequently designate in writing or within Hadari.</p>
  <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
    <li>Covered Entity: The primary email address associated with Covered Entity’s account in Hadari at the time notice is sent. </li>
    <li>HBS: legal@holisticbusinesssolutions.com</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Notice shall be deemed delivered on the date and time the email is transmitted, provided that the sending Party does not receive an automated notice of non-delivery, rejection, or invalid address. Communications, messages, comments, alerts, support tickets, and other operational correspondence transmitted through Hadari may be relied upon for routine account administration and day-to-day matters; however, such communications shall not constitute formal notice under this Business Associate Agreement unless this Business Associate Agreement expressly permits notice through Hadari.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">10. Term and Termination</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Term. This BAA becomes effective on the Effective Date and remains in effect until all PHI is returned or deleted in accordance with Section 7. Termination for Breach. If HBS materially breaches this BAA, the Covered Entity may provide written notice and an opportunity to cure within a reasonable period. If cure is not possible, the Covered Entity may terminate the GSA and this BAA immediately, or, if termination is infeasible, report the violation to the Secretary of Health and Human Services.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">11. Governing Law</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">This BAA shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of New York, without regard to its conflict-of-law principles, and applicable federal law. To the extent applicable, the Parties shall also comply with any state privacy or security laws that provide greater protection than applicable federal law. In the event of a conflict between this BAA and the GSA, the terms providing greater privacy or security protection shall control.</p>
  <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3">12. Execution</h4>
  <p class="text-gray-700">This BAA may be executed electronically or in counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original and together constitute one binding instrument. By checking the acknowledgment box after reviewing this Agreement in full, Client agrees to be legally bound by this Agreement. Electronic acceptance and associated system records, including date, time, IP address, and user account information, shall constitute Client’s signature and acceptance.</p>
